This was announced on ABC Radio news in Australia 3yrs.ago

@blueredbrick Also, high voltage DC apparently is a lot more dangerous than high voltage AC, in some ways. My best mate used to work for a company that serviced those old big floor-standing dot matrix printers for mainframes, the ones that could spit out several hundreds of pages a minute.
These things ran on 700VDC, with power supplies  capable of pushing out 50-100A, IIRC. They were very strict on safety protocols, because if you managed to get your body in the way of the current, all your muscles would contract, forcing you to fold over the equipment, and unable to pull away, at which point you just cooked.  They lost two technicians in the couple of years when he worked there. (this was in about 1985).
With AC, at least your muscles get flung in opposite directions at 50-60Hz, and you stand *some* chance of pulling away.

